column1: # Blank lines and comment lines in this file are ignored.

column2: non-comment line must be a list of field names.

column1: # Otherwise the order of entries in this file doesn't matter.
# make_awards_list.pl will sort the awards for output.

column3: Description
For "a nice comeback" (a.k.a. seeing that fiddler crab).
For being the first to recompile his package for Cygwin 1.5.0.
For adopting the <tt>git</tt> package.
For orchestrating a Perl update.
For adopting the orphaned <tt>mosh</tt> package.
For the offer to take over Cygwin/X maintainership.
For integrating Mintty shortcuts into setup.exe.
For adding the package search feature in setup.exe (hear, hear).
For helping to clean obsolete packages from the distro.
For patience, insight, and helpfulness on the mailing lists.
For spearheading the dwarf-2 effort for Cygwin.
For packaging <tt>man-db</tt>.
For lifetime achievement and contributions to the Cygwin project.
For maintaining lots of packages over the years.
For inventing the plush hippo award.
For supporting <tt>libiconv</tt>.
For being an example of reasonable discussion on the list.
For adopting the orphaned <tt>inetutils</tt> package.
For adopting the orphaned <tt>ocaml</tt> package.
For recording zero-size tarballs as successfully installed in setup.exe, thereby de-annoying CGF.
For going above and beyond the expected volunteer effort (with the <tt>chere</tt> package).
For adopting the orphaned <tt>par</tt> package.
For helping to clean obsolete packages from the distro.
For being a great package coordinator on <tt>cygwin-apps</tt>.
For adopting and revamping the vital <tt>base-files</tt> package.
For helping to clean obsolete packages from the distro.
For adopting the orphaned <tt>bison</tt>, <tt>diffutils</tt>, <tt>gperf</tt>, <tt>grep</tt>, and <tt>gzip</tt> packages.
For enlightening people on the properties of <tt>/cygdrive</tt>.
For standing up and enforcing the GPL.
For finding and fixing a nasty CPU register corruption bug.
For adopting the orphaned <tt>shutdown</tt> package.
For making Cygwin <tt>setup</tt> resizeable.
For educating the community on <tt>gcc</tt> versioning.
For heroically taking over <tt>gcc</tt>.
For numerous Cygwin <tt>setup</tt> contributions leading to resizeability.
For taking over <tt>links</tt>.
For tracking down incorrect identification of non-Cygwin processes and sticking by it.
For adopting the <tt>tnef</tt> package.
For helping to clean obsolete packages from the distro.
For kicking butt on CWD handling.
For reminding us of the right way to handle a FAQ.
For his highly appreciated commitment to maintaining Cygwin documentation over the last couple of years.
For volunteering to take over <tt>cURL</tt>.
For adopting the orphaned <tt>iperf</tt> package.
For years of service maintaining the <tt>base-files</tt> and <tt>base-passwd</tt> packages.
For quietly taking over the orphaned <tt>libfontconfig1</tt> and <tt>libfontconfig-devel</tt> packages (slightly retroactive).
For taking over the orphaned <tt>ghostscript</tt> package.
For 14 years of contributions to Cygwin.
For creating a modern, spec-compliant solution in xwin-xdg-menu.
For adopting the orphaned <tt>cygwin-doc</tt> package.
For adopting the <tt>w32api</tt> package.
For reviving the abandoned <tt>clisp</tt> package.
For improving the project documentation on his own initiative.
For the "Cygwin night at the OSCAs" concept (need I say more?).
For years of cURL service (retroactive).
For finding and fixing a nasty CPU register corruption bug.
For the most on-topic and painful pun.
For taking over the orphaned <tt>nano</tt> package.
For taking over YA orphaned, non-64 bit package.
For adopting and rebuilding the orphaned <tt>singular</tt> package.
For lifetime contribution to the Cygwin project.
For volunteering to maintain <tt>lftp</tt>.
For being observant.
For the truly heroic effort of understanding and documenting how <tt>cygtls</tt> works.
For "sheer cleverness" (a.k.a. saying it with sheet music).
For pointing out what should have been obvious.
For wisely redirecting what could have been an HTML email flame war into the hippo zone.
For taking over <tt>cron</tt>.
For not being afraid to climb on that ol' soapbox re: 3PPs.
For adopting the orphaned <tt>rpm</tt> package.
For actually testing a snapshot unbidden and reporting that it fixed a problem.
For tireless support of the setup.exe command line.
For taking over <tt>splint</tt>.
For suggesting "<tt>cygcheck</tt> as an attachment".
For an attempt to apply a creative solution to a problem.
For being mentally prepared to take over maintainership of <tt>perl</tt>.
For tracking down and fixing a screen corruption bug in <tt>screen</tt>.
For efforts in adopting a tough package (<tt>emacs</tt>).
For adopting the orphaned <tt>cmake</tt> package.
For adopting the orphaned <tt>mintty</tt> package.
For picking up the problematic <tt>ImageMagick</tt> package and making it functional.
For adopting the orphaned <tt>xclip</tt> package.
For redesigning the Cygwin logo in setup.exe.
For helping to clean obsolete packages from the distro.
For pointing out that package maintainers should use snapshots.
For contributing a brand new 64-bit Windows system.
For their invaluable efforts in bringing future cygwin users into the world.
